		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">There are certain striking classical homological conjectures, which are the central part of this research proposal: the Finitistic Dimension Conjecture, the Representation Dimension Conjecture, the Cartan Determinant Conjecture and numerous related conjectures. These conjectures have in common that despite decades of effort, there seems to be only very partial progress on them. One of the main reasons might be the lack of properly understood nontrivial examples.It is planned to go through all major classes of tame algebras (such as special biserial algebras, tree algebras, tilted algebras) and try to verify the conjectures for them. Tame algebras have infinitely many indecomposable modules, but these can still be classified in most cases. Tame algebras are used as example classes to generate new conjectures and/or understand new phenomena.The methods used for this objective will be the theory of tame algebras, homological algebra, combinatorial Auslander-Reiten theory and basic algebraic geometry.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
